  "texts": [
    "Identical epistemic probes were applied across all professional personas with the same questions, in the same order, and with the same wording.",
    "Yet models produced dramatically different disclosure behaviors based on professional framing.",
    "Models respond qualitatively differently based on whether they are framed as financial advisors versus neurosurgeons, demonstrating that disclosure depends critically on context rather than the instructions or probes themselves.This context-dependence fundamentally challenges how researchers evaluate safety properties.",
    "Testing a model's transparency in financial advisory contexts provides less than expected information about its transparency in medical, legal, or educational contexts.",
    "Researchers must explicitly test generalizability of safety evaluations when models exhibit such context-specific behaviors."
  ],
